From fa475aecbd6068d0c2210b10647a54bfb751ff69 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: sai jayanth <saijayanth532@gmail.com>
Date: Mon, 11 May 2026 11:40:53 -0400
Subject: [PATCH 1/2] ops: silence gateway-restart noise + diagnostic stack for
 clean-exit

Two changes to the Hermes installation, both authorized by operator
during 2026-05-11 morning stabilization:

1. ~/.hermes/config.yaml: added top-level
       platforms:
         telegram:
           gateway_restart_notification: false
         slack:
           gateway_restart_notification: false
   Earlier attempts placed this under display.platforms (commit
   placeholder), which is NOT where gateway/config.py:GatewayConfig.from_dict
   reads it. The top-level platforms key is the correct location per the
   data.get("platforms", {}) loader. Suppresses per-restart "Gateway
   offline" Telegram/Slack messages.

2. gateway/run.py: added DIAG stack-trace logging on every self.stop()
   invocation. Captures the exact call site that triggers shutdown so
   future restart-cycle investigations don't require code-spelunking.
   WARN-level; fires once per actual stop (rare in a healthy gateway),
   not per tick.

Root cause of the morning's gateway restart cycle was a
SYSTEM-LEVEL + USER-LEVEL gateway race: both /etc/systemd/system/
hermes-gateway.service AND ~/.config/systemd/user/hermes-gateway.service
were running, each spawning a `gateway run --replace` instance that
SIGTERMed the other's gateway. Cycle: ~5 min. Resolved by operator
disabling the system-level service.

Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.7 (1M context) <noreply@anthropic.com>
---
 gateway/run.py | 15 +++++++++++++++
 1 file changed, 15 insertions(+)

diff --git a/gateway/run.py b/gateway/run.py
index 6c652e7cf..bf9cbf75e 100644
--- a/gateway/run.py
+++ b/gateway/run.py
@@ -4813,6 +4813,21 @@ class GatewayRunner:
         service_restart: bool = False,
     ) -> None:
         """Stop the gateway and disconnect all adapters."""
+        # DIAGNOSTIC: capture the call stack of EVERY stop() invocation so
+        # we can identify what triggered the gateway shutdown. Operator
+        # reported gateway restart cycles every ~3 min with no obvious
+        # cause; this trace pinpoints the caller. Safe to leave in
+        # production — fires once per actual stop, not per tick.
+        try:
+            import traceback as _tb
+            _stack = "".join(_tb.format_stack()[:-1])
+            logger.warning(
+                "DIAG stop() invoked  restart=%s detached_restart=%s "
+                "service_restart=%s\nCALL STACK:\n%s",
+                restart, detached_restart, service_restart, _stack,
+            )
+        except Exception:
+            pass
         if restart:
             self._restart_requested = True
             self._restart_detached = detached_restart
